Package soot.jimple.infoflow.methodSummary.generator

Class SummaryGenerationTaintWrapper

  • java.lang.Object
    • soot.jimple.infoflow.methodSummary.generator.SummaryGenerationTaintWrapper
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ITaintPropagationWrapper
    public class SummaryGenerationTaintWrapper
extends Object
implements ITaintPropagationWrapper
    Taint wrapper to be used during summary construction. If we find a call for which we have no callee, we create a gap in our summary. This means that this taint wrapper needs to produce fake sources for the possible outcomes of the code inside the gap.
    Author:
    Steven Arzt

      • getTaintsForHashCodeEquals

        protected Set<Abstraction> getTaintsForHashCodeEquals​(soot.jimple.Stmt stmt,
                                                      Abstraction taintedPath)
        Gets the taints for hashCode() and equals() and other methods with default taints if the summary generator is configured to not summarizes these methods
        Parameters:
        stmt - The statement that might call a method with default taint
        taintedPath - The incoming taint abstraction
        Returns:
        The taint abstractions with which to continue the data flow analysis, or null if this method does not model the call. If the callee is handled, but no taint abstractions shall be propagated, this method returns an empty set.
